features.text: CRYPTO-FRENS is a more open and experimental collection of 100 1/1 pieces. Community goals are determined by the community members, creating their own goals in the discord channel. Join our discord, to become a part of the drknss-fam.
CRYPTO-JUNKIES is a small collection of 50 1/1 pieces with the goal to earn land in Cryptovoxels and do charity for street children.
These are some builds I made. If you click on the image it will teleport you there. If you click back on your browser you come back here.

CryptoPunks

10,000 unique collectible characters with proof of ownership stored on the Ethereum blockchain.

The CryptoPunks are 24x24 pixel art images, generated algorithmically. Most are punky-looking guys and girls, but there are a few rarer types mixed in: Apes, Zombies and even the odd Alien.

The project that inspired the modern CryptoArt movement. No two are exactly alike, and each one of them can be officially owned by a single person on the Ethereum blockchain. Originally, they could be claimed for free by anybody with an Ethereum wallet, but all 10,000 were quickly claimed. Now they must be purchased from someone via the marketplace that's also embedded in the blockchain.

Meebits

Say hello to The Meebits 20,000 unique 3D characters from the guys who made Cryptopunks.

The Meebits are 20,000 unique 3D voxel characters, created by a custom generative algorithm, then registered on the Ethereum blockchain.

The NFT contract the governs ownership is a standard ERC-721 that works with any compatible service or exchange.
Integrated No-Fee Marketplace

Also included in the contract is a custom marketplace that supports like-kind trading of up to 100 Meebits per transaction, along with all the standard buy, bid and ask transactions.

CryptoWiener - most leiwande collectibles!

The six-person artist collective CryptoWiener has been active in the NFT and Cryptoart Space since 2018, and with their early works they form a pioneering role in the emerging world of crypto art as one of the first projects in German-speaking countries. 

Website: https://cryptowiener.com/ 
CryptoVienna collection on Opensea: https://opensea.io/collection/cryptowiener-4 

With their first project CryptoWiener, the New Kids on the Block have stormed the metaverse in no time and brought a bit of Viennese color to the international blockchain scene. In the style of the well-known Cryptopunks, the Viennese have put the Viennese chic through the wringer with pixel characters and won the first Austrian Blockchain Award with their unique charm.
